id: pm-4os2
title: Contract schema golden-file must cover MCP tool inputSchema shapes — current snapshot only covers CLI flags
description: "tests/fixtures/contracts/full.json is the static gate for CLI contract drift (pm-d6kq). It covers command flag contracts and action availability but does NOT snapshot the TOOLS array from src/mcp/server.ts (tool names, inputSchema shapes, required fields, descriptions). A typo or refactor in TOOL_SCHEMA_BASE or any individual tool's inputSchema will pass the existing gate. Extending the golden file to include a MCP tool surface snapshot (names + required fields array) would catch regressions at CI before they reach agents."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: "area:contracts","area:mcp",quality
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:04:30.354Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-10T20:36:07.449Z"
author: audit-platform-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Contract golden-file snapshot includes each MCP tool's inputSchema shape\n- CI fails on unintended MCP inputSchema drift\n- `pnpm contracts:update` regenerates the expanded snapshot"
parent: pm-5k4v
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "buildMcpToolContracts() emits per-tool {name, description, required(sorted), input_schema} sorted by name as mcp_tools in contracts --full output, which scripts/contracts-snapshot.mjs captures into tests/fixtures/contracts/full.json; pnpm contracts:check (CI Gates static) fails on any MCP inputSchema drift."
expected_result: CI fails on unintended MCP tool schema drift before agents see it.
actual_result: "Golden file regenerated (+1046 lines, 25 tools); contracts-command.spec covers inclusion/omission/shape; pm_run schema-prop shrink is drift-locked."
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-10T15:14:14.958Z",mcp-tools-agent,"Contract golden file now snapshots the MCP tool surface. TOOLS moved out of src/mcp/server.ts into dependency-light src/mcp/tool-definitions.ts (only imports enum-contracts), exporting buildMcpToolContracts(): per-tool { name, description, required (sorted), input_schema (full shape) }, sorted by name. pm contracts --full --json emits it as mcp_tools (full projection only — exactly what scripts/contracts-snapshot.mjs runs), so tests/fixtures/contracts/full.json (+1046 lines, 25 tools) is regenerated by pnpm contracts:update and any inputSchema drift fails pnpm contracts:check inside CI Gates(static). Unit tests in tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts lock: full-output inclusion, brief/flagsOnly omission, required-field projections for pm_schema/pm_config/pm_append/pm_update/pm_run, shared TOOL_SCHEMA_BASE properties, and additionalProperties:true passthrough. Verified: pnpm contracts:update then contracts:check green; quality:static green."
